South Africa’s main stock index drops 0.2% as of 10:07 a.m. in Johannesburg, giving up an advance of as much as 0.7%, as a drop in bullion drags gold miners lower and a weaker rand weighs on banks. Markets in Asia had advanced as President Donald Trump’s departure from hospital eased concerns about his health, and amid optimism that lawmakers would move closer to providing more stimulus, boosting risk sentiment. An index of gold miners drops 1.1%, erasing an advance of as much as 0.7%. DRDGold Ltd. drops 2.9%, AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. is 1.3% lower, Harmony Gold Mining Co. falls 0.7%. NEWS: